7365922651124026656.video_description: Fish pie AKA Parmentier de poisson   Fish pie (4-6 portions) 600g Fish (diced) 50g Prawns ½ Fennel 1 Leek 1 Shallot 100g Button mushroom 40g Flour (plain) 100g Butter 400g Milk (whole) 150ml Cream (double 100g Peas (podded) 10g Dill (chopped) 1 Lemon (juice) Salt + pepper - 6 Potatoes 2 Egg (yolks) 75g Butter 75ml Milk (whole) Salt + pepper   - Sweat the fennel, leek, and shallot in the butter until soft (5mins). Add the sliced mushrooms and cook for another 3 minutes. Add the flour and cook out the roux for 2/3mins. - Slowly add the milk and cream, simmer for 2 minutes. Add the fish, peas, dill and lemon juice. Bring to the boil and top with mash potatoes. - Grill under hot grill until potatoes are nicely coloured 3-5 minutes.   #fish #pie #potato #pea #dill #fishpie #recipe
